WEBVTT

00:00.967 --> 00:01.301
ergreen Forest.

00:03.870 --> 00:06.239
Quiet, peaceful, serene.

00:07.841 --> 00:09.943
That is, until Bert
Raccoon wakes up.

00:09.943 --> 00:13.046
Yahoo!

00:14.280 --> 00:16.816
Yee-ha!

00:16.816 --> 00:18.218
Yipe!

00:18.218 --> 00:19.352
Oof!

00:24.224 --> 00:25.859
Luckily,
he has some good friends

00:25.859 --> 00:27.027
to help him out.

00:34.200 --> 00:36.903
Life would be simple in
the Forest except for:

00:38.138 --> 00:43.109
Cyril Sneer.

00:44.277 --> 00:46.413
And his life would
be simple except for:

00:46.413 --> 00:48.048
the Raccoons!

01:02.495 --> 01:05.131
When a new family moves
to the Evergreen Forest,

01:05.131 --> 01:07.200
it's cause for a celebration.

01:07.200 --> 01:09.636
And of course, no
party would be complete

01:09.636 --> 01:11.871
without Bert Raccoon.

01:11.871 --> 01:14.841
Hey, there's a lot
more out here, you guys!

01:14.841 --> 01:16.342
Not to worry, Nicole.

01:16.342 --> 01:18.711
We'll have you
unpacked in no time.

01:18.711 --> 01:22.215
Oh, my aching sacroiliac.

01:22.215 --> 01:24.818
I thought losing
my job was painful.

01:24.818 --> 01:26.419
Moving is worse!

01:26.419 --> 01:28.621
And standing still
won't get it done.

01:28.621 --> 01:29.856
Come on, big brother.

01:29.856 --> 01:31.191
Time's a-wasting.

01:31.191 --> 01:33.960
Gangway! Fragile
material coming through.

01:33.960 --> 01:35.628
Whoa!

01:35.628 --> 01:37.363
Interception!

01:37.363 --> 01:40.166
Pretty
good stunt, eh, George?

01:40.166 --> 01:42.068
Hey, how about a guest shot

01:42.068 --> 01:44.170
on that new TV show of yours?

01:44.170 --> 01:45.538
Give me a break, Bert.

01:45.538 --> 01:47.707
I haven't even started
my new job yet.

01:47.707 --> 01:49.509
Besides, there's not much call

01:49.509 --> 01:51.911
for daredevils on a
cooking show, Bert.

01:51.911 --> 01:53.513
Oh, I dunno.

01:53.513 --> 01:57.217
I could introduce a new recipe:

01:57.217 --> 01:59.385
"Dare-deviled eggs" (chortles).

02:00.520 --> 02:01.788
That sounds about right,

02:01.788 --> 02:03.456
coming from a canned ham.

02:04.390 --> 02:06.659
Fine, fine, I can take a hint.

02:06.659 --> 02:08.795
Are Bentley and
Lisa still upstairs?

02:08.795 --> 02:11.865
Yes, they're
still wheeling and dealing

02:11.865 --> 02:13.800
over who gets which bedroom.

02:13.800 --> 02:17.237
Oh, wait 'til Bentley
sees what I got him.

02:17.237 --> 02:20.340
An official Mammoth
Mudhens baseball cap!

02:21.508 --> 02:23.209
You always
get everything you want!

02:23.209 --> 02:25.211
And you're
acting like a big baby.

02:25.211 --> 02:27.480
Fine! Take the stupid room.

02:28.815 --> 02:30.083
See if I care!

02:30.083 --> 02:31.718
Uh, Bentley?

02:32.952 --> 02:34.387
And don't you dare
come back in here!

02:34.387 --> 02:36.589
Uh-uh-uh,
L-L-Lisa?

02:37.857 --> 02:39.492
I wish I still had
my old room, anyway.

02:39.492 --> 02:41.194
And I wish we'd
never even moved.

02:41.194 --> 02:43.830
So there!

02:43.830 --> 02:47.167
Sheesh, I wish I'd
stayed downstairs.

02:51.971 --> 02:53.206
In days of old,

02:53.206 --> 02:54.674
when there were no laws,

02:54.674 --> 02:56.543
Who did we count on?

02:56.543 --> 02:59.612
"Three
Guys With a Cause"!

02:59.612 --> 03:00.813
That's right, kiddies.

03:00.813 --> 03:02.549
Now, stay tuned to,

03:04.584 --> 03:07.086
Biff, Phil, and Alphonse:

03:07.086 --> 03:09.656
"Three Guys With a Cause",

03:09.656 --> 03:11.958
right here on K.N.O.X. TV.

03:13.459 --> 03:14.894
Oh, boy.

03:14.894 --> 03:19.599
I wish we had a life of
swash-buckling and derring-do.

03:19.599 --> 03:21.868
Yeah,
with the boss around,

03:21.868 --> 03:23.937
it's all buckling-down
and derring-don't.

03:27.140 --> 03:28.608
"You're cordially invited

03:28.608 --> 03:33.613
to visit my new television
facility, K.N.O.X. TV.

03:34.480 --> 03:37.450
Sincerely Yours, Mr. Knox."

03:37.450 --> 03:38.418
Fat chance.

03:38.418 --> 03:40.320
I'd sooner eat worms.

03:40.320 --> 03:43.690
Pigs! I've got something
else for you boys to shred.

03:43.690 --> 03:45.058
Will do, Boss.

03:45.058 --> 03:46.359
Put it on the pile.

03:48.261 --> 03:49.729
What was that, Boss?

03:51.698 --> 03:55.668
B-b-boys, I-I think
we're-we're done for!

03:56.603 --> 03:58.171
Ah! Ooh! Ai-ee!

03:58.171 --> 04:00.807
And if I ever see you three
thickheaded throwbacks again,

04:00.807 --> 04:03.276
I'll make you the main
attractions in a luau!

04:03.276 --> 04:05.278
And you won't be
wearing grass skirts.

04:06.212 --> 04:07.614
Show them to the gate, Snag.

04:08.448 --> 04:10.383
No, no!

04:15.922 --> 04:17.390
Hey, Lisa, look at this.

04:17.390 --> 04:19.459
They're giving away a
genuine Mudman Whirly-Bird

04:19.459 --> 04:20.660
in the Crackle Crunch.

04:20.660 --> 04:22.829
Sorry, Bentley,
it's not on the list.

04:23.763 --> 04:25.198
I never get anything I want.

04:25.198 --> 04:26.699
Aw, Lisa.

04:26.699 --> 04:30.003
It's only one measly
box of cereal.

04:30.003 --> 04:31.738
Until Dad starts his new job,

04:31.738 --> 04:33.640
we're on a tight budget.

04:33.640 --> 04:35.108
Poor little guy.

04:35.108 --> 04:38.177
All these changes
must be tough on 'im.

04:38.177 --> 04:41.014
Yeah, "poor little Bentley".

04:41.914 --> 04:43.316
Hello, boys.

04:43.316 --> 04:44.717
What can I do for you?

04:44.717 --> 04:46.819
I'm glad you
asked, Mr. Willow.

04:46.819 --> 04:48.855
As a result of recent cutbacks,

04:48.855 --> 04:53.626
we find ourselves available
for gainful employment.

04:53.626 --> 04:55.028
But we'd settle for a job.

04:56.262 --> 04:58.631
Well, I guess I
could use a trio

04:58.631 --> 05:00.667
of hardworking pack boys-

05:00.667 --> 05:01.901
Pack boys!

05:01.901 --> 05:04.037
Ha. We were hoping for something

05:04.037 --> 05:05.938
in the executive
management field

05:05.938 --> 05:07.173
at about 40K.

05:08.708 --> 05:11.678
Well, have you
tried the Want Ads?

05:11.678 --> 05:15.315
Oh, gee, thanks, Mr. Willow.

05:16.482 --> 05:19.519
Bentley, what are you
doing in these parts?

05:19.519 --> 05:22.622
Bentley and Lisa just moved
to the Forest, Mr. Willow.

05:22.622 --> 05:24.590
Isn't that grand!

05:24.590 --> 05:27.994
Bentley, you're going to
have a great time here.

05:27.994 --> 05:29.829
Uh, you too, Lisa.

05:29.829 --> 05:32.732
I see you're a
Mudhens fan, Bentley.

05:32.732 --> 05:34.367
What do you think of their
chances for the pennant?

05:34.367 --> 05:35.368
I think they'll take it.

05:35.368 --> 05:36.669
With Roland Nylon pitching,

05:36.669 --> 05:37.904
they can't lose!

05:37.904 --> 05:40.573
Uh, I'm a pretty
big basketball fan.

05:40.573 --> 05:42.742
Aw, gee, that's too bad, Lisa.

05:42.742 --> 05:45.044
There's no basketball
teams in the Forest.

05:45.044 --> 05:47.513
I figure the Diamondbacks
are the only threat

05:47.513 --> 05:48.548
the Mudhens have.

05:48.548 --> 05:49.782
Those wimps?

05:49.782 --> 05:51.718
Ha! No way.

05:51.718 --> 05:53.753
Not since they
traded Pony Fernando.

05:53.753 --> 05:56.622
Yeah, but they brought
up that new southpaw,

05:56.622 --> 05:58.291
Milk Can Floyd.

05:58.291 --> 06:00.626
Ah, he's a
designated do-nothing.

06:00.626 --> 06:03.196
It's
too good to be true!

06:03.196 --> 06:05.264
I call it fate.

06:05.264 --> 06:07.600
Well,
what are we waiting for?

06:07.600 --> 06:09.736
The perfect job awaits.

06:09.736 --> 06:11.070
Oh-hoo, yes!

06:14.340 --> 06:17.610
Where in tarnation did
those disorganized drips

06:17.610 --> 06:19.612
file the Bosco papers?

06:19.612 --> 06:21.447
Pigs! Front and,

06:22.315 --> 06:23.182
center.

06:23.182 --> 06:24.517
Hi, Pop.

06:24.517 --> 06:26.085
Pigs got the day off?

06:26.085 --> 06:27.820
Who? Oh, right.

06:27.820 --> 06:28.654
The Pigs (chortles).

06:28.654 --> 06:30.123
I fired them.

06:30.123 --> 06:32.358
Should have done it years ago.

06:32.358 --> 06:34.260
You're kidding, right, Pop?

06:34.260 --> 06:35.194
Kidding?

06:35.194 --> 06:36.829
Why I should have fired them

06:36.829 --> 06:39.298
before they messed
up my filing system.

06:39.298 --> 06:42.468
Uh, maybe it's not too
late to get them back, Pop.

06:42.468 --> 06:45.872
If you think I'd take those
goldbricking galoots back

06:45.872 --> 06:48.708
then your calculator
needs batteries, Cedric.

06:48.708 --> 06:50.543
Now, if you'll excuse me, son,

06:50.543 --> 06:52.211
I'm kind of busy.

06:52.211 --> 06:56.549
Bosco, Bosco, where is
that dang blasted file?

06:58.050 --> 07:01.721
"To the best boss in the world."

07:01.721 --> 07:03.055
Gosh.

07:03.055 --> 07:08.060
Yeech! I've told those
idiots a million times:

07:08.060 --> 07:11.097
No jelly sandwiches
in the office!

07:11.097 --> 07:12.799
But Mr. Knox,

07:12.799 --> 07:15.134
I moved my whole
family to the Forest

07:15.134 --> 07:16.869
on the strength of your letter.

07:16.869 --> 07:20.206
Well, that's very
unfortunate, sir.

07:20.206 --> 07:23.609
All I said was I'd
like to try you out

07:23.609 --> 07:26.145
as the host of "Chef Surprise".

07:26.145 --> 07:27.346
Now see here, Mr. Knox-

07:27.346 --> 07:28.481
Hold on, Ralph.

07:28.481 --> 07:29.849
I'll handle this.

07:29.849 --> 07:32.418
So you're telling me
this is a trial period?

07:32.418 --> 07:33.619
Exactly.

07:33.619 --> 07:36.489
If your ratings are
good on the first show,

07:36.489 --> 07:40.526
I'd be more than happy
to offer you a contract.

07:40.526 --> 07:42.361
Don't worry, sir.

07:42.361 --> 07:46.365
I'm sure things'll
work out just fine.

07:46.365 --> 07:49.435
Now if you'll excuse me.

07:49.435 --> 07:52.271
Aw, don't worry
about it, George.

07:52.271 --> 07:53.473
You'll get the job.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.308
And what if I don't?

07:55.308 --> 07:57.543
How can I tell
Nicole and the kids?

07:57.543 --> 07:58.511
I've uprooted them,

07:58.511 --> 08:00.012
taken the kids out of school,

08:00.012 --> 08:02.114
brought them to a strange place.

08:02.114 --> 08:05.184
And now I'm not even
sure I've got a job.

08:05.184 --> 08:07.887
Sure made a mess of things
this time, Ralphie old boy.

08:07.887 --> 08:10.323
A real mess.

08:12.725 --> 08:14.427
I must confess,

08:14.427 --> 08:19.432
I was unaware you three were
trained actors and stuntmen.

08:20.800 --> 08:22.468
Ah, y-you wouldn't
believe some of the stunts

08:22.468 --> 08:25.004
we've pulled, uh, Mr. Knox, sir.

08:25.004 --> 08:29.375
Well, I certainly hope
your audition works out.

08:29.375 --> 08:32.778
It would give me great
pleasure to hire away

08:32.778 --> 08:36.516
three of Mr. Sneer's employees.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.384
In fact, I dunno how
you managed to work

08:38.384 --> 08:41.954
for such a money-grubbing
slave driver for this long.

08:41.954 --> 08:44.991
You can't talk about
our boss that way.

08:44.991 --> 08:46.058
I (elbow thumps) ow.

08:46.058 --> 08:48.127
Uh, our, uh, ex-boss.

08:48.127 --> 08:50.730
Yeah, um, uh, well,

08:50.730 --> 08:54.267
he could be difficult
at times (chortles).

08:54.267 --> 08:55.968
By the way, um,

08:55.968 --> 08:58.971
what happened to the
last, uh, "Three Guys"?

08:58.971 --> 09:00.139
Huh?

09:00.139 --> 09:02.742
Oh, a couple of
months in a body cast

09:02.742 --> 09:05.077
and they'll be right as rain.

09:05.077 --> 09:07.246
Well, let's get on
with it, shall we?

09:07.246 --> 09:10.383
Okay, boys, action!

09:16.289 --> 09:19.492
I think you boys are
gonna work out just peachy.

09:19.492 --> 09:22.295
I was
afraid he'd say that.

09:23.663 --> 09:26.666
Oh, everything's
fine, I guess.

09:26.666 --> 09:28.301
I'm popping over to
the Raccoondominium.

09:28.301 --> 09:29.669
Want to come along?

09:29.669 --> 09:30.736
No, thanks, Mom.

09:30.736 --> 09:32.238
Have fun.

09:32.238 --> 09:33.606
Sorry about that.

09:33.606 --> 09:35.808
Uh, how's the basketball
team doing without me?

09:36.776 --> 09:38.411
They won?

09:38.411 --> 09:41.414
Gee, that's-that's great.

09:41.414 --> 09:42.381
You have to go?

09:42.381 --> 09:43.449
Oh no, no.

09:43.449 --> 09:44.917
I've got lots to do.

09:44.917 --> 09:46.586
Say hi to everybody for me.

09:47.420 --> 09:48.654
'bye.

09:48.654 --> 09:49.889
We're off to the
ballgame, Lisa.

09:49.889 --> 09:51.390
Wanna come?

09:51.390 --> 09:52.925
No thanks, Bentley.

09:52.925 --> 09:54.560
I still have to
unpack some stuff.

09:54.560 --> 09:56.696
You know, Bert, I think
living in the Forest

09:56.696 --> 09:59.198
is gonna suit me just fine.

09:59.198 --> 10:01.233
Yeah, just fine.

10:02.902 --> 10:05.938
♪ We would stand on
Saturday nights ♪

10:05.938 --> 10:09.275
♪ The boys and me in line ♪

10:09.275 --> 10:14.280
♪ Fighting for the chance
to dance with you ♪

10:15.781 --> 10:19.018
♪ I can still remember ♪

10:19.018 --> 10:22.288
♪ The look upon your face ♪

10:22.288 --> 10:27.293
♪ You were so surprised
that I told you ♪

10:28.060 --> 10:31.330
♪ All life long ♪

10:31.330 --> 10:34.266
♪ I knew it was forever ♪

10:34.266 --> 10:37.903
♪ All life long ♪

