♪ I knew we couldn't stop ♪

10:40.706 --> 10:44.410
♪ All life long ♪

10:44.410 --> 10:47.279
♪ I knew it was forever ♪

10:47.279 --> 10:52.251
♪ All life long ♪

10:54.954 --> 10:58.190
♪ They still go back there ♪

10:58.190 --> 11:01.427
♪ Most Saturday nights ♪

11:01.427 --> 11:06.432
♪ The same old band
in gray and blue ♪

11:07.600 --> 11:09.535
♪ And I can still remember ♪

11:09.535 --> 11:10.603
♪ Still remember ♪

11:10.603 --> 11:14.440
♪ You and the boys in line ♪

11:14.440 --> 11:18.878
♪ And I still want
to dance with you ♪

11:26.352 --> 11:28.054
♪ Whoa ♪

11:28.054 --> 11:30.956
♪ All life long ♪

11:30.956 --> 11:33.759
♪ I knew it was forever ♪

11:33.759 --> 11:37.396
♪ All life long ♪

11:37.396 --> 11:40.232
♪ I knew we couldn't stop ♪

11:40.232 --> 11:43.769
♪ All life long ♪

11:43.769 --> 11:46.739
♪ I knew it was forever ♪

11:46.739 --> 11:50.376
♪ All life long ♪

11:50.376 --> 11:53.079
♪ I knew we couldn't stop ♪

11:53.079 --> 11:57.116
Bosco, Bosco, it's got
to be in here somewhere.

11:57.116 --> 11:58.984
I don't know what's worse:

11:58.984 --> 12:01.454
living with the Pigs
or living without them.

12:01.454 --> 12:03.155
I hate computers!

12:05.391 --> 12:07.827
Pop, you'll never
guess what's on TV!

12:07.827 --> 12:10.429
A vast wasteland, I suppose.

12:10.429 --> 12:11.697
Watch this.

12:11.697 --> 12:12.832
In days of old,

12:12.832 --> 12:14.233
when there were no laws,

12:14.233 --> 12:15.968
who did we count on?

12:17.403 --> 12:20.206
"Three Guys With a Cause"!

12:20.206 --> 12:24.510
Bob, Alphonse,
the king's men pursueth me.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.446
Uh, quickly, Biff,

12:27.446 --> 12:31.584
lest their approach signal
our ultimate (screams).

12:31.584 --> 12:33.886
Aren't the Pigs great, Pop?

12:33.886 --> 12:34.954
And to think,

12:34.954 --> 12:36.922
we knew them way back when.

12:38.124 --> 12:43.062
I-I'm really happy for
them, son, really happy.

12:44.263 --> 12:46.098
They seem to be doing
just fine without me.

12:50.836 --> 12:52.404
Bentley seems
to be having fun.

12:52.404 --> 12:55.474
He and Bert are cooking up
all kinds of things to do.

12:55.474 --> 12:57.843
I wish I could settle
in as easily as the kids.

12:57.843 --> 12:59.378
I mean, look at Lisa.

12:59.378 --> 13:01.947
She acts like she's lived in
the Forest all her life, huh.

13:01.947 --> 13:03.182
Well, that's Lisa.

13:03.182 --> 13:05.384
She's always been so popular.

13:05.384 --> 13:08.187
I guess she knows she'll
have no problem fitting in.

13:08.187 --> 13:10.189
Yeah, but I might.

13:10.189 --> 13:11.423
About the job, Nicole.

13:11.423 --> 13:12.458
Do you think I should tell them?

13:12.458 --> 13:13.592
Tell them what?

13:13.592 --> 13:14.794
Oh, Lisa.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.562
Ah, this is a
little tough honey,

13:16.562 --> 13:19.465
but, uh, I saw Mr. Knox, and-

13:19.465 --> 13:20.833
What your father's
trying to say

13:20.833 --> 13:24.270
is the job isn't guaranteed.

13:24.270 --> 13:26.372
Let's just keep this
to ourselves for now.

13:26.372 --> 13:28.207
I don't want Bentley to worry.

13:28.207 --> 13:29.041
Okay, honey?

13:29.041 --> 13:31.177
Bert, Bentley!

13:31.177 --> 13:32.511
Dinner's almost ready!

13:32.511 --> 13:33.412
Be right there!

13:34.713 --> 13:36.916
Wait 'til Lisa sees
this, little buddy.

13:36.916 --> 13:38.417
She's gonna love it!

13:38.417 --> 13:40.653
Professor Smedley-Smythe
thinks there might be a job

13:40.653 --> 13:41.887
for me at the museum.

13:41.887 --> 13:44.523
And I think azaleas
would be nice out front.

13:44.523 --> 13:46.225
I'll ask Lady
Baden-Baden about it.

13:46.225 --> 13:48.627
You remember the time
Old Man Brothers caught us

13:48.627 --> 13:49.428
in the orchard?

13:49.428 --> 13:50.830
He caught you, George.

13:50.830 --> 13:53.232
I was always the fast
one in our family.

13:53.232 --> 13:56.001
And then we can go
camping up on Freen's Peak.

13:56.001 --> 14:00.239
Oh, and wait 'til you see
the Endless Echo Caverns!

14:00.239 --> 14:01.507
Oh, I almost forgot.

14:01.507 --> 14:04.376
I've gotta show you
my baseball cards.

14:04.376 --> 14:05.911
You're not sayin' much, Lisa.

14:05.911 --> 14:07.713
Uh, how was your day?

14:07.713 --> 14:10.182
Lousy, as if you care.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.550
What's wrong, Lisa?

14:11.550 --> 14:13.252
Everything!
Everything's wrong.

14:13.252 --> 14:14.553
I've got no friends anymore,

14:14.553 --> 14:15.788
I miss my school,

14:15.788 --> 14:16.722
I hate this house!

14:16.722 --> 14:17.990
That's enough, young lady!

14:17.990 --> 14:19.859
We've all got a lot
of adjusting to do.

14:19.859 --> 14:20.693
Oh, sure.

14:20.693 --> 14:21.961
Everyone else is happy.

14:21.961 --> 14:23.696
Nobody cares what I think!

14:23.696 --> 14:24.897
None of this would have happened

14:24.897 --> 14:26.398
if you hadn't have
lost your job.

14:26.398 --> 14:29.101
Lisa!

14:29.101 --> 14:30.603
It's all your fault!

14:30.603 --> 14:33.706
And I hope you don't get that
stupid job at the station!

14:37.977 --> 14:39.411
How's Lisa doing?

14:39.411 --> 14:41.380
She won't talk to us.

14:41.380 --> 14:43.415
Maybe she just needs some time.

14:43.415 --> 14:46.752
Hmm, you mind if I
take a whack at it?

14:46.752 --> 14:48.120
It can't hurt.

14:48.120 --> 14:49.488
Maybe she'll listen to you.

14:53.893 --> 14:56.061
And Bert breaks
out of the pack, and wham-o!

14:56.061 --> 14:57.897
Slam dunk!

14:57.897 --> 15:00.466
And it's a swisher from
the three-point line!

15:02.501 --> 15:03.903
Hiya, Lisa.

15:03.903 --> 15:05.304
Hey, watch me.

15:05.304 --> 15:07.239
You might learn something
about the fine art

15:07.239 --> 15:08.574
of slam-dunkin'.

15:08.574 --> 15:11.143
Whoa, argh!

15:11.143 --> 15:13.712
Lisa?

15:19.818 --> 15:23.022
Wah! Oof!

15:24.990 --> 15:28.560
You can't teach me a thing
about basketball, buster.

15:32.831 --> 15:37.603
But-but, did, uh, oof!

15:59.658 --> 16:00.893
Whew!

16:00.893 --> 16:03.329
You must have won the
high school championship

16:03.329 --> 16:04.863
all by yourself.

16:04.863 --> 16:06.465
Don't be silly, Bert.

16:06.465 --> 16:08.934
Basketball has to
be a team effort.

16:08.934 --> 16:12.404
Oh, kind of like
a family, right?

16:12.404 --> 16:14.673
Yeah, exactly like a...

16:15.607 --> 16:18.310
Yeah, a lot like a family, Bert.

16:19.678 --> 16:22.214
"Three Guys With a Cause",

16:22.214 --> 16:25.451
Scene 10, Take 13.

16:26.986 --> 16:29.722
Thirteenth try
lucky, eh boys?

16:34.560 --> 16:35.661
No, no, no!

16:36.795 --> 16:40.532
You're supposed to
land in the hay cart!

16:40.532 --> 16:42.735
In the hay cart!

16:42.735 --> 16:46.205
Oh, believe me, Mr.
Knox, we're trying.

16:46.205 --> 16:47.573
We're trying.

16:47.573 --> 16:49.108
That's it.

16:49.108 --> 16:51.910
If you boys can't provide
the sort of action I need-

16:51.910 --> 16:53.345
Ahem.

16:53.345 --> 16:55.714
Why, Mr. Sneer.

16:56.815 --> 17:00.185
I'm so glad you
accepted my invitation

17:00.185 --> 17:03.222
to visit my extensive studio.

17:03.222 --> 17:04.556
It's the Boss.

17:04.556 --> 17:07.259
Maybe
he wants us back.

17:07.259 --> 17:08.560
Dream on.

17:08.560 --> 17:11.563
that part of our lives
is over and done with,

17:11.563 --> 17:13.599
and we might as well face it.

17:15.067 --> 17:19.038
So (clears throat) the Pigs
giving you a hard time, Knox?

17:19.038 --> 17:20.672
Boil my grits.

17:20.672 --> 17:22.174
No, sir.

17:22.174 --> 17:26.278
They are exemplary employees.

17:26.278 --> 17:29.081
Come and say hello
to my "Three Guys".

17:30.516 --> 17:34.586
Ooh, uh, they might even
deign to sign an autograph.

17:35.754 --> 17:38.223
Wouldn't
that be a thrill.

17:38.223 --> 17:39.324
Three Xs.

17:39.324 --> 17:41.794
Hi, Boss! Uh, Cyril.

17:41.794 --> 17:43.195
Hello, boys.

17:43.195 --> 17:44.229
How are things?

17:44.229 --> 17:45.998
Hunky dory, Boss.

17:45.998 --> 17:49.234
We're having the time
of our lives, thanks.

17:49.234 --> 17:50.836
That's great, boys!

17:50.836 --> 17:54.006
Um, (coughs) you-you
left these behind.

17:54.873 --> 17:56.375
Oh, Boss.

17:56.375 --> 18:00.145
I-I thought you
might want them.

18:00.145 --> 18:02.548
Our bunny-wunnies!

18:02.548 --> 18:06.618
I know you always liked
your, uh, bunny-wunnies.

18:06.618 --> 18:08.220
All
right, we're not

18:08.220 --> 18:10.222
shooting a soap opera, here.

18:10.222 --> 18:12.157
Places, everyone.

18:12.157 --> 18:15.461
Uh, would you like to
stick around and watch?

18:15.461 --> 18:17.729
Sure. Thanks, I will.

18:17.729 --> 18:20.065
Camera Three,
zoom in on that logo.

18:21.733 --> 18:22.734
Aw, Nicole.

18:22.734 --> 18:24.036
What if I bomb?

18:24.036 --> 18:25.270
What if I don't get the job?

18:25.270 --> 18:27.306
I wish none of this
had ever happened.

18:27.306 --> 18:30.275
Well, it did happen
and we'll get through it.

18:31.677 --> 18:34.847
We're all going to be out
there rooting for you, George.

18:34.847 --> 18:35.781
Hi, Mom.

18:35.781 --> 18:36.715
Hi, guys.

18:36.715 --> 18:39.451
Oh, I wish Lisa had come.

18:39.451 --> 18:40.919
Me, too.

18:40.919 --> 18:42.754
And now,
ladies and gentlemen,

18:42.754 --> 18:44.723
it's time for
everybody's soon-to-be

18:44.723 --> 18:48.994
fabulously favorite cooking
show, "Chef Surprise",

18:48.994 --> 18:52.931
starring George Raccoon!

18:52.931 --> 18:54.933
Good afternoon, folks.

18:57.536 --> 18:59.638
And
welcome to the show.

18:59.638 --> 19:02.374
Battering
ram sequence, Take One.

19:02.374 --> 19:06.278
Action!

19:12.851 --> 19:16.155
Ahem. Headache,
Knox?

19:16.155 --> 19:19.191
And to
celebrate my first show,

19:19.191 --> 19:22.528
Every audience member can
take home one of these pies.

19:22.528 --> 19:24.863
But first, we'll just finish up

19:24.863 --> 19:28.233
our chocolate cherry
cheesecake supreme.

19:28.233 --> 19:30.435
By the way, this is my
daughter's favorite.

19:31.603 --> 19:33.605
Well, would a member
of our studio audience

19:33.605 --> 19:36.241
care to sample it?

19:36.241 --> 19:37.576
I will!

19:39.211 --> 19:40.679
Lisa!

19:40.679 --> 19:41.947
I'm sorry, Daddy.

19:41.947 --> 19:43.215
Aww.

19:43.215 --> 19:44.750
Fellas,
fellas, in this one,

19:44.750 --> 19:48.320
you're trying to get away
from the king's men, okay?

19:48.320 --> 19:49.454
Hit it!

19:51.957 --> 19:53.325
Whoa!

19:53.325 --> 19:56.595
No, no, you
pea-brained pork bellies!

20:01.033 --> 20:03.569
Mm, this is the best-

20:07.406 --> 20:09.041
You're fired!

20:09.041 --> 20:10.142
Ya hear me?

20:10.142 --> 20:14.479
Fired!

20:15.314 --> 20:16.515
Take that, sir!

20:16.515 --> 20:17.816
Oof!

20:17.816 --> 20:18.650
Ha-ha!

20:18.650 --> 20:20.452
What's going on, here?

20:20.452 --> 20:21.553
Bombs away!

20:22.888 --> 20:25.724
Oh, George, your show,
c'est (pie splats) ooh!

20:27.192 --> 20:28.026
Oh!

20:30.195 --> 20:30.996
Well, you can't
say I didn't try.

20:30.996 --> 20:31.863
More pies, sir?

20:33.065 --> 20:34.933
Ha-ha, I haven't
had this much fun

20:34.933 --> 20:36.969
since my last tax refund.

20:36.969 --> 20:38.637
We-we make a pretty good team,

20:38.637 --> 20:40.539
r-right, Boss?

20:40.539 --> 20:42.441
I've seen worse.

20:42.441 --> 20:46.178
Uh, Boss, about that little
accident with the shredder?

20:46.178 --> 20:49.214
It's coming out
of your salary.

20:49.214 --> 20:50.616
You mean,

20:50.616 --> 20:53.752
we can have our old jobs back?

20:53.752 --> 20:55.220
Might as well.

20:55.220 --> 20:57.089
I wouldn't wish you
three messed-up meatballs

20:57.089 --> 20:59.458
on anyone else, heh!

20:59.458 --> 21:02.628
Stay tuned, folks, for
more "Chef Surprise".

21:05.664 --> 21:07.799
It takes
courage to face the future

21:07.799 --> 21:09.601
when you leave your past behind.

21:10.636 --> 21:11.570
For a while,

21:11.570 --> 21:13.038
Lisa didn't know where to look

21:13.038 --> 21:14.506
for the strength she needed,

21:14.506 --> 21:17.342
until Bert Raccoon
helped her find it:

21:17.342 --> 21:18.577
in her family.

21:18.577 --> 21:20.379
It looks pretty
official to me!

21:20.379 --> 21:22.514
After that
double-dip disaster,

21:22.514 --> 21:26.251
I still can't believe Mr.
Knox gave me the contract.

21:26.251 --> 21:29.988
Well, the show is called
"Chef Surprise", Dad.

21:29.988 --> 21:33.558
Welcome to the
Evergreen Forest!

21:34.493 --> 21:37.029
Gangway! Here comes the pie!

21:41.433 --> 21:43.435
Was it something I said?

21:45.470 --> 21:47.272
♪ Ooh ♪

21:58.984 --> 22:01.920
♪ When darkness falls ♪

22:01.920 --> 22:05.891
♪ Leaving shadows in the night ♪

22:05.891 --> 22:08.593
♪ Don't be afraid ♪

22:08.593 --> 22:12.564
♪ Wipe that fear
from your eyes ♪

22:12.564 --> 22:15.634
♪ If a desperate love ♪

22:15.634 --> 22:19.738
♪ Keeps on driving you wrong ♪

22:19.738 --> 22:22.574
♪ Don't be afraid ♪

22:22.574 --> 22:26.278
♪ You're not alone ♪

22:26.278 --> 22:29.481
♪ You can run us ♪

22:29.481 --> 22:33.885
♪ We've got
everything you need ♪

22:33.885 --> 22:36.521
♪ Run with us ♪

22:36.521 --> 22:40.892
♪ We are free ♪

22:40.892 --> 22:43.395
♪ Come with us ♪

22:43.395 --> 22:47.866
♪ I see passion in your eyes ♪

22:47.866 --> 22:50.435
♪ Run with us ♪
